snippet.textDisplay:
This has to be called out, at best this is a draw. All Might is completely knocked out, and Might Guy is as good as dead. But the real issue is this ... Wiz and Boomstick really doesn't understand what multiplier actually do.

In the case of All Might ...that 60 times multiplier from current All Might to when he was at his best is a BAD estimate. Because when All Might was at his best was before his battle with All-for-one and we actually can't calculate that power All-for-one doesn't scale to anyone in the Naruto Universe (power wise). All-for-one had a collection of OP quirks combined in him and even though All-for-One did severely damage All Might ... All Might still "won" by defeating the jerk. Key point was they were both damaged but not killed.

Now, for Might Guy and his gates. After the sixth gate is opened, the damage to Might Guy's body is exponentially greater. Gate 6 boils his blood and damages his blood vessels which is why he uses it only in emergencies. Gate 7 starts to damage his bones on a microfracture level.
